  "local_port": 58076,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Are there any websites like DAAD for masters in US?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several organizations and websites that provide information and resources for international students looking to pursue master's degrees in the United States, similar to the DAAD (German Academic Exchange Service) for Germany. Here are some notable ones:\n\n1. **EducationUSA**: A U.S. Department of State network that provides information about U.S. higher education, including guidance on finding and applying to schools, visa procedures, and financial aid.\n\n   Website: [EducationUSA](https://educationusa.state.gov)\n\n2. **Institute of International Education (IIE)**: This organization offers resources about study abroad opportunities, scholarships, and support for international students.\n\n   Website: [IIE](https://www.iie.org)\n\n3. **Scholarships.com**: A comprehensive scholarship database that includes information on scholarships available for international students studying in the U.S.\n\n   Website: [Scholarships.com](https://www.scholarships.com)\n\n4. **GradSchoolHub**: Offers information on graduate programs, including rankings and advice for international applicants.\n\n   Website: [GradSchoolHub](https://www.gradschoolhub.com)\n\n5. **Council of Graduate Schools (CGS)**: Provides resources specifically for graduate education, including policies, research, and best practices related to graduate schools.\n\n   Website: [CGS](https://cgsnet.org)\n\n6. **College Board**: Known for SAT and AP exams, College Board also offers resources for finding colleges and funding your education.\n\n   Website: [College Board](https://www.collegeboard.org)\n\n7. **FindAMasters.com**: A platform focused specifically on master's degree programs, providing a searchable database of programs around the world, including the U.S.\n\n   Website: [FindAMasters](https://www.findamasters.com)\n\n8. **Peterson's**: Offers information about graduate programs, test preparation, and scholarships for students aiming to study in the U.S.\n\n   Website: [Peterson's](https://www.petersons.com)\n\nWhen exploring these resources, make sure to look for information specific to your field of interest and any scholarship opportunities available for international students.",
